The paper deals with security aspects of the Index Coding with Side Information (ICSI) problem, which involves coding and transmission of messages over a network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The focus on security and coding schemes further supports the likelihood of cs.CR and cs.IT.
